S|# 09 · Production Calendar (Long-form)|> The date-based view of the long-form cnt machine — when each video is scripted, filmed, edited, and published, so cadence is visible at a glance.
S|Purpose|A calendar layout over the cnt pl so the owner can see cnt scheduled across days/weeks and confirm the publishing cadence (e.g. 1 video/week) is being met. It is the "Calendar" counterpart to the cnt pl's Kanban.
S|What it shows (inferred from context)|- A weekly/monthly grid with cnt cards placed on their target dates (filming days, edit days, publish dates). // - Each entry tied to a cnt pl card and its stage (Scripting → Filming → Editing → Ready → Published). // - Cadence/health at a glance: gaps in the schedule are visible, so the owner can keep the funnel full.
S|Relationship to other screens|- Shares data with **cnt pl** (`08`) — same cards, different (date) view, reachable via that page's **Calendar** toggle. // - Distinct from **Scheduler** (`15`), which schedules *soc posts* across platforms; the prd Calendar is about *long-form video prd*. // > **Confidence:** Listed in the sidebar (LONG-FORM section) and referenced via the cnt pl's "Calendar" view, but not shown as a dedicated full screen in the captured screenshots. Layout above is *inferred* from its name and role.